    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">794A.5/7–2350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-23T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 23, 1950—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Delivered message to Foreign Minister Yeh this noon as instructed by <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 61, July 22.</p>
                <p>He requested me reply that Chinese Government intends observe its commitment,
                    that only violation has been unfortunate incident involving British ship<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d220fn1">The incident referred to involved the strafing of the
                        British motor vessel <hi rend="italic">Glenearn</hi> by Chinese Nationalist
                        Air Force planes on July 15 resulting in the wounding of two crew
                        members.</note> for which Chinese Government offered apology and
                    compensation and that Chinese Government preparing <pb facs="0402" n="388"
                        xml:id="pg_388"/> memorandum for ComSeventhFlt regarding Communist attacks
                    on small islands off mainland.</p>
                <p>Apart from foregoing, Yeh indicated Chinese Government considering withdrawal
                    from Chinmen despite “great importance to both China and US”. Plan calls for
                    mining of waters around Amoy and holding aircraft in readiness defend evacuation
                    in event Chinese Communist air force attempts intervene.</p>
                <p>Also passed to Yeh substance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 55, July
                    21.</p>
                <p>Yesterday informed Chen Tai-Chu accordance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 56, July 21<note n="2" xml:id="d220fn2">See footnote 1 to
                        telegram 74, July 17, from Taipei, <ref target="#pg_381">p.
                        381</ref>.</note> and reiterated to Yeh today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
